r the chips are poured, the bag is set upright behind the filled bowl. A hand reaches into the bowl and takes some chips, leaving the Fritos package standing as a background display. The view then moves closer to the package until the “Fritos” logo dominates the screen. The brand name fills the image, and the printed phrase “MADE TO MUNCH” appears along the bottom as the product identity is emphasized.\n\nThe cartoon children return, now close up and smiling as they eat. The striped-shirt boy faces forward with a huge grin and a chip in his mouth, then swallows and smiles contentedly. Another child, seen in profile, raises a chip to his mouth and chews with a pleased expression. The girl then appears in close profile, holding a chip delicately between her fingers, opening her mouth wide to eat it, and then smiling with satisfaction.\n\nThe scene widens to the three cartoon children gathered around a table with the Fritos bag standing open in the center. The striped-shirt boy is behind the bag, taller than the others, smiling with his hands near the jagged top of the package. The girl stands on the right side of the bag, holding and eating a chip. The smaller child stands on the left, reaching up eagerly. All three appear happy and absorbed in snacking. The bag’s front again shows the large “Fritos” name.\n\nAs the children continue munching, the smaller child on the left grins with eyes closed and hands clasped near his chest, looking blissful. The striped-shirt boy leans forward and glances toward him, while the girl pauses and looks on. Then the striped-shirt boy throws his head back with a big open-mouth laugh or delighted reaction. The girl laughs too, and the small child keeps enjoying the chips. The children resume reaching for the bag from both sides: the smaller child stretches up toward the opening, the girl leans in from the right, and the striped-shirt boy stands proudly behind it.\n\nThe commercial ends with the Fritos bag enlarged at the center of the picture. The children’s hands and partial faces remain around the edges, but the package takes over the image. The jagged open top, the bold “Fritos” logo, horizontal stripe design, and lower printed “Fritos” name are clearly visible, leaving the final visual focus on the product bag.",
